{
  "texts": [
    "4.5) highlights that the company's disclosures impact ESG scores more than other financial aspects or company characteristics.",
    "Disclosing several ESG topics (category entropy) positively affects ESG scores, whereas fewer disclosed ESG topics hurt scores.",
    "This data-driven insight accordingly confirms that transparency on non-financial information rewards companies' ESG assessment [63,66].",
    "The analysis of Sect. 4.5 also confirms the negligible impact of governance-related topics towards ESG scores in comparison to social-and environmental-related topics such as Human Rights, Energy and Waste.",
    "The findings of Sect. 4.5 also unveil that disclosing many actions related to the ESG topics Employee Development and Energy negatively impact ESG scores."
  ]
}